4. General Best Practices for All Queues

•	Audit and Monitor: Enable logging and monitor access and usage.
•	Rotate Credentials: Regularly rotate passwords, keys, and tokens.
•	Validate and Sanitize Messages: Never trust message content; validate and sanitize before processing.
•	Dead-Letter Queues: Use dead-letter queues to handle failed message processing securely.
•	Limit Message Size: Restrict message size to prevent abuse or denial-of-service attacks.
•	Patch and Update: Keep your message broker and client libraries up to date.